# Test cases for `list-rolls`

## Successfully listing all rolls from XML

```console
$ filmrolls list-rolls -r tests/data/filmrolls.xml
? success
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 ID      Frames   Film                         Camera                  Loaded                       Unloaded
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 A0012   1        Ilford Delta 100 @ 100/21°   Voigtländer Bessa R2M   2016-03-28 15:16:36 +00:00   2016-05-21 14:13:15 +00:00
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

```

## Trying to use a non-existent XML file

```console
$ filmrolls list-rolls --color=never -r /path/which/does/not/exist.xml
? failed
error: Invalid value for --film-rolls <FILE>: Could not open "/path/which/does/not/exist.xml": No such file or directory (os error 2)

Usage: filmrolls list-rolls [OPTIONS] <--film-rolls <FILE>>

For more information, try '--help'.

```

## Trying to use a garbage XML file

```console
$ filmrolls list-rolls --color=never -r /dev/null
? failed
Error: 
   0: Failed to read roll data from "/dev/null"
   1: Unexpected `Event::Eof`

Backtrace omitted. Run with RUST_BACKTRACE=1 environment variable to display it.
Run with RUST_BACKTRACE=full to include source snippets.

```
